  "footnotes": [
    "First Battle of Kosovo (1389): Fought between a Christian coalition under Prince Lazar and the Ottoman army of Murad I; both rulers died in battle. The outcome was indecisive but led to Serbian vassalage.",
    "Second Battle of Kosovo (1448): Decisive Ottoman victory over John Hunyadi of Hungary; ended Christian hopes of reversing Ottoman expansion in the Balkans.",
    "Great Turkish War / Holy League (1683–1699): Habsburg-led alliance drove Ottomans from much of Hungary and briefly occupied Belgrade (1688–1690); ended by Treaty of Karlowitz.",
    "Great Migration of the Serbs (1690): After Habsburg retreat, Patriarch Arsenije III led ~30,000–500,000 Serbs northward into Habsburg territory, reshaping the demographic map of Kosovo and Vojvodina.",
    "Government of National Salvation (Nedić regime, 1941–44): Serbian collaborationist administration under Milan Nedić; operated alongside German Military Administration.",
    "Kosovo declaration of independence (2008): Recognised by over 100 states including the US and most EU members; Serbia, Russia, and China do not recognise it. ICJ advisory opinion (2010) found the declaration did not violate international law."
  ]
